# Quadratus Femoris

> The **quadratus femoris** is a flat, square-shaped deep external rotator of the hip, connecting the [[Ischial Tuberosity]] to the intertrochanteric crest of the [[Femur]].

## 🔗 Key Connections
- **Origin** — [[Ischial Tuberosity]] of [[Hip Bone]] (lateral aspect)
- **Insertion** — Intertrochanteric crest of [[Femur]]
- **Nerve** — Nerve to quadratus femoris (L4, L5, S1)
- **Action** — Hip external rotation + adduction

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **Ischiofemoral impingement** — Quadratus femoris compressed between lesser trochanter and ischial tuberosity
- **Quadratus femoris tear/oedema** — Seen on MRI; hip pain + external rotator weakness

